claims:
5. A method for detecting a small molecule-protein interaction, the method comprising:
expressing a virus-like particle (VLP)-forming polypeptide or a fusion protein comprising a VLP-forming polypeptide in a cell;
recruiting a fusion construct comprising first and second small molecules covalently linked to one another, wherein the first small molecule interacts with the VLP-forming polypeptide or a fusion protein and the second small molecule interacts with at least one polypeptide other than the VLP-forming polypeptide or fusion protein, to said VLP-forming polypeptide;
interacting a polypeptide other than the VLP-forming polypeptide or fusion protein with the second small molecule to the fusion construct;
isolating the VLPs; and
analyzing an entrapped complex in an isolated VLP.
